                    <idno type="FIEY">181</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1257-2">male</sex>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1257-2">Actes syriaques : I.E. Rahmani, Acta sanctorum confessorum Guriae et Shemonae
(Rome, 1899) ; Burkitt, Euphemia, 3* -25*, 90- 110 ; BHO, 363.
Homelie metrique de Jacques de Saroug: AMS, I, 131- 43; BHO, 366.
Documents armeniens : BHO, 364-65.
Suhada ', I, 100- 101.
DHGE 129- 30 (1980) , 1193- 94 (J.-M. Sauget).
Autres references dans OCA 236 (1988), 195 n. 1.
P. Devos, "La liste martyrologique des textes du Guria et Shamona", AB 90 (1972),
15-26.
P. Chiesa, "11 dossier agiografico Iatino dei Santi Gurias, Samonas e Abibos", Aerum
65 (1991), 221-58.
BS, VII, 539- 43 (J .-M. Sauget) .
Un couvent sous le patronage de Guria existait pres de Seert : cf. Fiey, Nisibe,
224- 25.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1257">
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1486">Shmona</persName> and Guria were two martyrs
          who were killed in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> during
          the Diocletian persecution. There was great devotion to these saints in Edessa.</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1257-1" source="#bib1257-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Guryo w-Shmuna is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/1634">Euphemia and the Goth (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1257-2" source="#bib1257-2">
